But since the late nineties, these domains have increasingly been taken over by celebrities from the world of acting, music and most recently, reality television. 

Cindy claims that appearing on magazine covers and in advertising campaigns was of little interest to actresses back in the day because they wanted to seen as serious artists. 

She said: 'The reason supermodels could come into being was because Hollywood actresses wanted to be taken seriously - they didn't want the red carpet to be a catwalk, which it has now become.'

