She continued: 'And the models were like, "We'll do that!" And all of a sudden fashion wasn't just about Vogue and couture, there was an explosion of coverage and we were the rock stars of that.' 

Since those early days, the fashion world has managed to produce a couple of supermodels in the forms of Gisele Bundchen and Kate Moss. 

And more recently, Cara Delevingne has emerged head and shoulders above the rest of the new breed of models, bagging contracts with everyone from Topshop to Burberry. 

